   Anthrax and the Bioterrorism Threat

   The following links will provide you with useful information about
   anthrax including details about the disease, recommended treatment, and
   specific indicators used to recognize anthrax symptoms in emergency
   departments.
     * FBI Suspicious Letter and Package Advisory*
     * Questions and Answers About Anthrax*
     * Anthrax and Bioterrorism Fact Sheet*
     * Senate Hearing On Terrorism Through the Mail (Testimony by Dr. Ivan
       C.A. Walks)
     * What You Should Know About Anthrax*
     * Suggested Protocol for Inhalation Anthrax Evaluation in Emergency
       Room*
     * Environmental Test Results for Area Post Office Facilities*
     * DC Area Anthrax Patient Summary*
     * Centers for Disease Control (CDC) Anthrax Information
     * Current DOH Recommendations for People Potentially Exposed to
       Anthrax in Mail-Handling Facilities*

   For more information, contact the DC Department of Health's Anthrax
   Information Hotline at (866) 501-1097.

   For general information, view these helpful links:

     * DC Department of Health (DOH) Website
     * Federal Bureau of Investigation (FBI) Website
     * United States Postal Service (USPS) Website
     * Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) Website

   The CDC has also established a CDC Public Response Hotline:

     English (888) 246-2675

                              Spanish (888) 246-2857

   * These documents are presented in Portable Document Format (PDF). A
   PDF reader is required for viewing. To download a reader, please click
   here. If you are having trouble reading these files, please click here
   for additional information.

